Description:
GRAND AND ELEGANT FAMILY ABODE
Situated in the heart of Drysdale, this superb family home has been built with pride and sits gracefully on approx. 1273m2 parcel of land overlooking lush green fields. This extensive home features multiple living spaces on a grand scale including a unique central atrium courtyard, a delightful formal lounge with ornamental fireplace, open plan kitchen, meals, family room and a parents retreat upstairs with balcony. French doors are featured throughout the home leading onto multiple balconies, with the main outdoor entertaining area flowing out from the open plan living room and kitchen. The upstairs Master bedroom is spacious and features WIR and full size ensuite and enjoys access to the upstairs living area and central atrium, giving natural light through the home. 3 further bedrooms with BIR's and home office contribute to the size and elegance of this home. An enormous 6 car garage underneath the home has to be seen to be appreciated and can easily accommodate multiple cars, a large boat and a full sized caravan.

Description:
Spacious, Solid & Centre of Town
Nestled in amongst a small number of townhouses is a solid, spacious two-bedroom ground level residence in Drysdale. This property will appeal to downsizers or weekenders seeking a secure, stress-free, low maintenance gem.
Beyond the front security door is an inviting, carpeted living area with a gas wall-heater and ceiling fan. Through the sliding door is the sleeping quarters with two very spacious double bedrooms with built-in robes and a large and central bathroom that accommodates a bath, shower, vanity and toilet.
Flow through to the light filled dining room and generous kitchen complete with a breakfast bar, walk-in pantry, Fisher & Paykel dishwasher and Westinghouse wall oven and four-burner stove top. Sliding doors lead to an undercover patio for barbeques and clothes hanging space.
Other features include a laundry, study nook or sewing bench. remote-controlled one and a half car lock-up garage with work benches and second toilet. This space would suit all handy people and craftspeople.
Only a short walk to the Drysdale village, with grocery stores, medical centres, community centres and beside Drysdales beautiful parklands and lakes.

RARELY OFFERED ON MARKET, COMMUNITY LIFESTYLE
Retirees/Investors, delight in this impressive three bedroom home situated within the prestigious 'Belleview' complex that provides the perfect neighbourly community in a quiet, secure setting. The perfect private oasis.
Home comprises open plan living, kitchen and dining area opening out to undercover courtyard area. Well-designed kitchen with island bench and breakfast bar. Other features include gas ducted heating, split system air conditioning, drive through garage, screen door and much more.
Lovely garden aspect. Located across from the local recreation area within minutes to all that Drysdale has to offer.

Description:
Prime Drysdale Location
Situated close to the main shopping centre, local primary school and public transport. Look no further than this solid brick veneer home. The vendors are keen to consider realistic offers. Just waiting for the new owner to bring it back to its former glory this grand older home is situated in a prime Drysdale location. Positioned away from the front of the block it sits in a commanding position on the substantial 725m2.
Comprising three generous sized bedrooms all with built in storage, a spacious lounge, dining and original kitchen. This home has been well cared for over the years. Also located in the rear yard is a self-contained bungalow - great for visiting family and friends or alternatively a great studio surrounded by established trees.
Plenty of yard space and a single car garage makes this property well worth a look.

Description:
Contemporary Living in Rural Surrounds.
Located in a tightly held pocket of Drysdale, this home offers contemporary and luxe living in a sought-after rural location.
Situated upon a generous 764m2 battle-axe allotment, this 12-month young, Long Island Home offers a free-flowing floor plan, perfectly zoned with the growing family in mind.
Upon entry to the home, you are welcomed by an automatic sense of Hamptons luxury, with a light and bright neutral palette and stylish ¾ dado walls. The lavish master bedroom sits at the fore of the home, equipped with walk-in-robe and ensuite with vanity, oversized shower and separate toilet, while the 3 remaining bedrooms occupy the rear and are all spacious in size, complete with built-in-robes. Fitted with quality fixtures and fittings, the kitchen boasts stainless steel 6 burner gas cooktop, electric oven, dishwasher, walk-in-pantry, with additional pantry in the adjoining laundry and stone benchtops. The kitchen overlooks the vast open plan living and dining area and offers seamless indoor/outdoor entertaining, with access to the large undercover deck. A 2nd separate living room flows from this open plan area with a feature wall mantle and cozy electric fire, while offering access via sliding doors to the back garden.
A clever study nook sits central to the 3 rear bedrooms, which are serviced by the main bathroom offering shower, tiled in bath, vanity and separate toilet, while the spacious laundry with amply storage and outdoor access completes this amazing family home. Extra features include ducted heating, split system and DLUG with external access.
The undercover outdoor deck is equipped with built-in cabinetry and makes for seamless indoor/outdoor entertaining all year round. The front and back gardens are both established and low maintenance with a large grassed back area also on offer.
Often sought but rarely found, this home offers a unique opportunity with its rural and private location. With the heart of Drysdale and The Bellarine's major amenities only a short drive away and with the region's best Primary and Secondary schools, as well as the Drysdale Station and Historic Bellarine Rail Trail being quite literally at your fingertips, don't miss this chance to secure a new-near home in an exclusive pocket of Drysdale.
*All information about the property has been provided to Hayeswinckle by third parties. Hayeswinckle has not verified the information and does not warrant its accuracy or completeness. Parties should make and rely on their own enquiries in relation to this property.

Description:
PRIME VILLAGE SPOT, A GREAT ENTERTAINER AND SOLAR .
This lifestyle property will suit the astute buyer,. With private indoor and outdoor spaces it is perfect for entertaining or as a quiet retreat. A large open plan space includes dining, a well equipped kitchen and space for a family lounge, all opening to a wonderful undercover patio....with pizza oven, barbeque, cupboards and bench space. The main lounge room can close to create a quiet area with a cosy gas log heater. Three bedrooms, the master is more like a retreat with ensuite, full dressing room and space to sit , two others have BIR'S. The study has built in shelves, could easily be turned into fourth bedroom/nursery. Central bathroom, laundry and separate toilet. Features include dishwasher, pantry, 900m stove, central heating, fans, zip clip blinds, quality furnishings and fittings. A 3kw solar system takes advantage of the premium feed in tariff, and is complimented with solar hot water. Drive through double garage and separate workshop as well as mature leafy gardens. A lifestyle gem in the heart of Drysdale on the Bellarine Peninsula with wineries , culinary delights, open spaces and the magic bay!

Description:
Serene Estate
A lifestyle opportunity enabling you to thrive and prosper in an intimate residential estate. Residing in this enviable location offers a lifestyle of coastal living, the convenience of a large regional centre within a 20 minute drive and designed around a semi rural, close knit community with every convenience at your doorstep.
The peninsula location is renowned for the idyllic, outdoor lifestyle. Spend a day at the beach, go fishing or enjoy a glass of your favourite wine at one of our many local wineries. The Port Phillip Ferry sails twice daily from Portarlington to South Bank if you fancy a day trip to the city. You will ask yourself why you didn't make the move sooner.
Ground works to commence late 2018.
Selling fast, contact Rhonda Humpage 0457 313609

Description:
Amazing home for the active large family!
Sitting on approx 1310m2 and on 2 titles this impressive property has a lot to offer the large, active family or tradesman. Comprising 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 2 living plus study, extensive outdoor entertaining area and DLUG. Central heating ceiling fans throughout and evaporative cooling provides all year round comfort. A swimming pool and spa, in addition to the large shed, complete what is an amazing package. The layout of the home has the study at the front and the master bedroom with walk in robe and ensuite. Moving further into the home is the formal lounge then through to the central hub of the home which is a wonderful large open plan kitchen, dining and lounge. The remaining bedrooms are located on the southern side of the home and feature built in robes and ceiling fans. From the central hub sliding doors open to the extensive paved outdoor courtyard and pool area. On the norther side of the property is the fantastic shed (11x6.7m) which is currently being used as a gym/man cave but offers options galore. With a large roller door it would be an ideal workshop or additional garaging for cars. Properties like this are rare to the market particularly so centrally located close as it is to the Drysdale shopping village and Christian College. With all this lovely property has to offer it is well worth a closer look!

Description:
Boutique Living
With the heart of Drysdale township only 200 metres away and within walking distance to all major amenities, this neat as a pin home is located in the ever-popular boutique Central Walk Estate. With quality fixtures and fittings, this Glenville built home situated upon a 425m2 block offers a neutral, modern and clean crisp palette throughout.
First impressions count and this low maintenance and immaculate front garden will impress. The spacious master bedroom sits at the fore and offers a stunning custom corner window, which allows natural light to stream through, while complete with walk-in-robe and ensuite with stone benchtop vanity, shower and toilet. Flowing down the main hallway, the galley style kitchen offers stainless steel gas cooktop, electric oven, dishwasher, tiled splash back and is fitted with quality stone bench tops and island bench. The kitchen overlooks the expansive and sundrenched living and dining space, equipped with split system and ducted heating for all year comfort and offering effortless indoor/outdoor entertaining, with sliding door access to the undercover outdoor pergola.
Cleverly zoned, the rear of the home hosts the 3 remaining bedrooms with built-in-robes and ceiling fans, a centrally located bathroom with shower, tiled in bath and vanity with stone bench top. The separate toilet and laundry with outdoor access complete this ideal package.
Perfect as is, the back garden offers a calm and tranquil retreat to enjoy the rural outlook on offer or personalise as you desire, this low maintenance, fresh canvas offers an inviting grass space with external access from the DLUG.
An ideal opportunity for first home buyers, downsizers looking for that central location or a smart investment for all you savvy investors (with a potential rental return of $430 p/w) this home is a true standout in this most sought after location in Central Walk Estate. Located in the heart of the Bellarine Peninsula, Central Walk Estate is within close proximity to the beautiful cosmopolitan city of Geelong, university campuses, world class beaches, natural bushland, boutique wineries, restaurants, golf and sailing clubs as well as local amenities, child-care facilities and schools at your fingertips. With all this and more, it is the ideal lifestyle choice that many are seeking!

Description:
Period Charm in the Heart of Drysdale
Charming and tranquil, this awe-inspiring splitlevel abode will encapsulate you from the moment of entry. Set upon a generous 799m2, this is a rare opportunity to secure a unique character home, in a highly sought-after pocket and located only moments to the centre of Drysdale.
Offering an Edwardian inspired frontage, the low maintenance, flower lined front garden path leads you to a quaint front veranda. Once inside, the warmth of the timber hardwood floors, high ceilings and a neutral palette are imminent. Cleverly zoned and offering a versatile, free flowing floor plan, the front wing of the home offers 2 generously sized bedrooms, both with built-in-robes, a versatile 4th bedroom/study, an open lounge space which effortlessly flows into a 2nd sitting area, equipped with the delight of a Coonara wood fire. The enormous master retreat sits on the top level of the home and must be seen to be believed! Equipped with walk-in-robe, ensuite with timber-top vanity, shower and toilet and all complete with its own split system for year-round comfort. The kitchen offers gorgeous blackwood timber cabinetry, electric cooking, dishwasher, island bench and all complete by an expansive walk-in-pantry. Stepping down and freely flowing from the kitchen, you're welcomed by a sun filled 2nd living area, with garden views and sliding door access to the back wrap around verandah and outdoor entertaining. A central bathroom with shower, bath and vanity, separate toilet and fully equipped laundry completes this beautiful home.
The established and private back garden is in a league of its own! Offering a beautiful and picturesque wrap around verandah, courtyard style outdoor entertaining, an open grassed space, bird aviary, side access from the front single car port, a 6x8.9 lock up garage and offering rear access, it has everything you need and more!
Additional features of the home include; timber hardwood floors, plantation shutters, 2 split systems, ducted heating, roman blinds, ceiling fans and a water tank. Another bonus of this unique opportunity is the potential for immediate positive cash flow with the option to continue running the successful AirBnB that is currently in place. With the home so flexible and versatile, it offers itself as the perfect holiday home or for those needing a dual occupancy set up.
With all major amenities, supermarkets, public transport, golf clubs, boat ramps and eateries at your fingertips and with the region's best Primary and Secondary schools only a short stroll away, this highly sought-after pocket of Drysdale offers the best of everything.
